<p style="line-height: 1.2; word-break: break-word; font-size: 14px; mso-line-height-alt: 17px; margin: 0;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"> </span></p>
<p style="line-height: 1.2; word-break: break-word; font-size: 14px; mso-line-height-alt: 17px; margin: 0;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><a href="https://drsophiayin.com/blog/entry/dog-bite-prevention-dogs-bite-when-humans-greet-inappropriately/" rel="noopener" style="text-decoration: underline; color: #0068A5;" target="_blank">Dogs Bite when Humans Greet Inappropriately</a></span><br/> <br/><span style="font-size: 14px;"> Thank you for viewing our safety information regarding rescue pups, we hope you found it informative. OPH wants to ensure that dogs find families who are prepared to take on this big responsibility! We believe that following these guidelines can lead to a happy and safe lifestyle for everyone involved! Please feel free to reach out to us if you have any questions.</span><br/> <br/><span style="font-size: 14px;"> When you have a moment, would you please reply that you have received this email and reviewed the information with your children or children that you interact with?</span></p>
